The ''[[yen]]'' sense came much later in the {{w|Meiji period}}, from {{bor|ja|zh|sort=えん|圓|tr=yuán}}, itself from {{m|zh|銀圓|tr=yínyuán||round [[silver#Adjective|silver]] object(s), ''especially'' a [[piece of eight]]}}. Compare {{cog|zh|元|tr=yuán||[[yuan]]}} and {{cog|ko|원||Korean [[won]]}}.

The ''yen'' became the official currency of Japan in 1871, succeeding the {{m|ja|両|tr=ryō}} and the {{m|ja|文|tr=mon}}.

